channel.description: The latest CVEs for IBM -- Engineering Test Management

item.title: CVE-2021-29668|2024-09-17T02:42:44.006Z -- ibm -- engineering%20test%20management
item.description: IBM Jazz Foundation and IBM Engineering products are vulnerable to cross-site scripting. This vulnerability allows users to embed arbitrary JavaScript code in the Web UI thus altering the intended functionality potentially leading to credentials disclosure within a trusted session. IBM X-Force ID: 199406.

item.title: CVE-2020-4974|2024-09-17T01:41:02.443Z -- ibm -- engineering%20test%20management
item.description: IBM Jazz Foundation products are vulnerable to server side request forgery (SSRF). This may allow an authenticated attacker to send unauthorized requests from the system, potentially leading to network enumeration or facilitating other attacks. IBM X-Force ID: 192434.
